<item>
            <title>[PIG-3805] ToString(datetime [, format string]) doesn&apos;t work without the second argument</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3805</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The exec function of ToString is written to handle 1 or 2 arguments (it defaults to ISO, which is consistent with ToDate).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the getArgToFuncMapping function returns only one FuncSpec, requiring the formatString argument.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To fix: just return add another FuncSpec to getArcToFuncMapping.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
